We’ve seen a slight decrease in unemployment—small, but in a depression this deep, any break from Brüning’s deflationary orthodoxy is a welcome change.

The following day, however, Papen issues a decree allowing employers to undercut wages set by collective bargaining agreements when hiring new workers, instantly sparking outrage among the <span style="color: #c00000;">socialist</span> and <span style="color: #000000;">Christian</span> trade unions.